er\nphase transition at a noise amplitude $\\eta_c>0$ that is proportional to $v$,\nand that scales approximately as $\\eta_c \\sim v \\, (-\\ln v)^{-1/2}$ for $v \\ll\n1$. These results show that the motion of particles is able to sustain a state\nof global order in a system with voter-like interactions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Feb 2021 14:33:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:51:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-15"}
